title: Man Utd news: Roy Keane takes huge swipe at 'cocky' Jose Mourinho | Metro News
text:
Chris Davie for Metro.co.uk Thursday 23 Feb 2017 7:44 am Roy Keane has taken a swipe at Jose Mourinho’s conduct. (Getty Images) 
Roy Keane is unhappy that Jose Mourinho is ‘back to his old cocky self’ at Manchester United . 
The 54-year-old initially struggled to get consistent results in his early stages at Old Trafford but now appears to have found his rhythm, with United losing just once in all competitions since the beginning of November. 
Mourinho guided United to the last-16 of the Europa League on Wednesday evening, while he has the chance to secure his first trophy at Old Trafford by beating Southampton in Sunday’s EFL Cup final. 
But Keane is unhappy with the way the United manager is conducting himself. Keane says Mourinho should show more humility. (Getty Images) 
Asked if Mourinho now has his swagger back, Keane told ITV: ‘It’s a pity really, you’d like to see bit more humility. 
‘You knew once they started winning a few games he’d get back to his old cocky self.’
